        "creatureType": "",
        "details": {
            "description": "<p>Mogaru brushes against a structure, severely compromising the building's stability and possibly causing it to collapse.</p>",
            "disable": "<p><span data-pf2-check=\"athletics\" data-pf2-label=\"Brace the Structure DC\" data-pf2-dc=\"43\" data-pf2-show-dc=\"gm\">Athletics</span> (master), <span data-pf2-check=\"crafting\" data-pf2-label=\"Brace the Structure DC\" data-pf2-dc=\"43\" data-pf2-show-dc=\"gm\">Crafting</span>(master), or <span data-pf2-check=\"engineering-lore\" data-pf2-label=\"Brace the Structure DC\" data-pf2-dc=\"43\" data-pf2-show-dc=\"gm\">Engineering Lore</span> (master) to brace the structure to reduce the risk of collapse until the end of the creature's next turn. The DC of the flat check for this round (see Routine) is increased by 4 on a success, or by 8 on a critical success. Increasing the flat check DC to 21 or higher stabilizes the structure, ending this hazard.</p>",
            "isComplex": true,
            "level": {
                "value": 15
            },
            "reset": "<p>The building becomes susceptible to Shake Apart again [[/r 1d6]] rounds after it is stabilized.</p>",
            "routine": "<p>(1 action) The GM rolls a DC 9 flat check to determine if the building collapses, increasing the DC as listed above. On a successful check, dust and debris fall within the building and 30 feet around it, providing concealment and dealing [[/r 6d6 # bludgeoning damage]]{6d6 bludgeoning damage} to [[/r 1d4]] randomly chosen targets (<span data-pf2-saving-throw=\"reflex\" data-pf2-traits=\"damaging-effect\" data-pf2-label=\"\" data-pf2-dc=\"35\" data-pf2-show-dc=\"gm\">basic Reflex</span> save; on a critically failed save, the creature is knocked @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Prone]{Prone}). On a critical success, the effect is the same, but the debris deals [[/r 12d6 # bludgeoning damage]]{12d6 bludgeoning damage} to [[/r 2d4]] randomly chosen targets instead (<span data-pf2-saving-throw=\"reflex\" data-pf2-traits=\"damaging-effect\" data-pf2-label=\"\" data-pf2-dc=\"35\" data-pf2-show-dc=\"gm\">basic Reflex</span> save; on a critically failed Reflex save, the creature is restrained by rubble until freed [Force Open DC 38, Escape DC 35]).</p>"
        },
